<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/23065278-argie-maniati"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1471687845i/23065278._UY100_CR9,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/23065278-argie-maniati">Argie Maniati</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Yes!! There is always some connection between the characters although each book has different protagonists!!! Sometimes they appear briefly in previou<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Yes!! There is always some connection between the characters although each book has different protagonists!!! Sometimes they appear briefly in previous books or are mentioned at some point. Not always though. The relation is always different and i won't say anything else because my description of this series always turns out quite spoilery...<br /><a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
